title: Triumph Diagnostic Tool - New Diagnostic Features for Off Road Motorcycles

body.body: Triumph Diagnostic Tool - New Diagnostic Features for Off Road Motorcycles
New diagnostic tool features have been released for the above model(s). The new features are detailed below.
Triumph Diagnostic Tool features for the above model(s) are only available to approved Off Road motorcycle dealers.
The following Service tools are required to connect the diagnostic tool to the above model(s).
Live Data sets for the above model(s) are divided into the following groups.
- displays the live Throttle Position Sensor Voltage as well as the Learned Minimum Throttle Position Voltage.
- displays a list of sensor parameters available over an open OBD diagnostic session.
- displays a list of sensor parameters available over a secure diagnostic session.
- displays the Push Button Position, and Push Button LED Status for each of the left hand handlebar switches.
A printable PDF Live Data Report can be generated by clicking the
button while viewing the Live Data.
The History Data area displays information on how long the motorcycle has been operated under various conditions over its lifetime.
History Data sets for the above model(s) are divided into the following groups.
- Displays the total engine run hour counter.
- Displays how long the motorcycle has been operated under various throttle position ranges.
- Displays how long the motorcycle has been operated under various engine speed ranges.
- Displays how long the motorcycle has been operated under various engine temperature ranges.
- Displays how long the motorcycle has been operated under various air temperature ranges.
- Displays how long the motorcycle has been operated under various battery voltage conditions.
- Displays the minimum and maximum battery voltages detected by the ECM over the vehicle lifetime.
A printable PDF History Report can be generated by clicking the
button while viewing the History Data.
The Adjust area provides guided adjustment processes for the following:
Learn Minimum Throttle Position - This must be done when replacing the Engine ECM or Throttle Bodies on the above model(s).
Adjust Idle Speed - This feature can be used to adjust engine idle speed to optimal RPM range.
Write VIN - This feature is only available for replacement Engine ECMs and must be done when fitting and commissioning a replacement.
Select the Adjust feature you require, then click Start and follow the onscreen instructions.
This process can only be performed by approved Off Road motorcycle dealers.
The Engine ECM on the above model(s) also provides a 'Dealer Lock/Unlock' function.
This function enables dealers to lock the motorcycle and prevent the engine from being started, after the initial Transit Lock has been cleared at PDI.
The feature can be used to lock motorcycles if they are to be kept in dealer storage after PDI has been completed.
The Dealer Lock function does not require further authorisation or entry of an unlock code.
Care must be taken to ensure that both the Transit and Dealer locks have been unlocked on the above motorcycle(s) before handover to the customer.
To set the Dealer Lock to Locked:
Use the pull down menu to change the Dealer Lock Status to
screen and confirm the Dealer Lock Status is reported as Locked.
The Malfunction Indicator Lamp (MIL) will flash on and off slowly when the Dealer Lock is set.
Return to the diagnostic tool Main Menu.
Disconnect the diagnostic interface and all diagnostic interface adapters from the motorcycle.
Check the motorcycle is locked by attempting to start the engine.
The engine may start on the first attempt after setting the dealer lock.
If the engine starts on the first attempt, turn the engine off and wait for 30 seconds.
Attempt to start the engine again. The engine will crank when the engine start button is pressed, but it should no longer start.
To Set the Dealer Lock to Unlocked:
Follow steps 1 to 3 in the dealer locking procedure above, but set the Dealer Lock Status to
screen and confirm the Dealer Lock Status is reported as Unlocked.
After unlocking, the MIL should return to normal operation and it should be possible to start the engine.
